               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18381022-name-1200" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18381022-name-1200" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18381022-name-1200" type="surname" value="WILLIAMS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18381022-name-1200" type="given" value="PETER"></interp>PETER WILLIAMS</persName>
                  </hi>. I come from Newport in Monmouth shire, and am master of a vessel. The prisoner was in my employ foe fifteen days—the vessel arrived in the river Thames on Friday night, the 5th of October—I went into my cabin between ten and eleven o'clock, took off my clothes, and hung my watch on a little pin by my bed-side—my money was in my trowsers' pocket in a bag—when I awoke in the morning I missed my watch and money—my mate went for the prisoner to the forecastle where he slept, and he and his clothes were gone—this is my watch and bag—(<hi rend="italic">looking at them</hi>)—the money has not been found.</p>
